# System files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Environment variables (Angular & NestJS)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.*.example
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.*.example

# NOTE: environment.ts / environment.prod.ts under src/environments/ are intentionally NOT
# gitignored. They hold no real secrets in this repo (just the API base URL + public OAuth
# client IDs — see comments in those files), and environment.ts must be committed anyway:
# Angular's fileReplacements swaps its *contents* at build time but still needs the file to
# physically exist for module resolution, even in a fresh clone (this broke the first Vercel
# deploy — the file was gitignored, so a clean `git clone` had no environment.ts at all).
# If a real secret is ever added to either file, split it out into a separate gitignored file.
